data.title: About Jenelle — Osborne for Lompoc Mayor
data.text:
Jenelle Osborne…

was elected to Lompoc City Council in November 2016 and Mayor in 2018, 2020 and 2022. She is 57 years old and has been a resident of Lompoc since 2000 with her husband, Jason Osborne, a physicist and Principal Engineer with Bruker Nano, in Goleta. Izzy, a Brittany Spaniel, joined the family in 2022. Jenelle has a Bachelor of Science in History with a focus on public administration, graduating summa cum laude, from Texas Woman’s University. As a small business owner since 2005, Jenelle provides event planning and professional organizing services. She has dedicated the past eight years to being a member of Lompoc’s city council and mayor. Her service on various committees and commissions across the local, state, and national level has been vital to Lompoc’s success and change.
